16/07/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- The commander of the Turkish NATO-led contingent in Afghanistan has died in a road accident in Afghanistan's northern province of Faryab, the Turkish Foreign Ministry announced on Wednesday (July 15th). Colonel Faruk Sungur and his driver died late Tuesday night. Two other soldiers in the vehicle were injured. (Zaman - 16/07/09; Anadolu news agency, Press TV, AFP - 15/07/09)
